{
  "name": "Month 1.6 - Zone 2 Cadence Changer",
  "note": "This session,similar to the strength-endurance efforts are designed to get you used to producing the power at different cadence ranges, the higher cadences work your cardiopulmonary system much more than a lower cadence effort. You will see your heart rate rise during the high cadence element despite the power remaining the same. This session is also good at simulating bunch-riding and having to accelerate your cadence quickly without changing power too much.\n   (by trainSharp)",
